title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Sauer P6  Bundespolizei Pistol
postcontent: The P6 was Sig's competitor for the 1970's German Police pistol upgrade, and was widely accepted due to manufacturing quality and cost over the Walther P5 and the H&K P7 "squeeze cocker". It is a special version of the Sig P225 with upgrades to the hammer and a firmer hammer spring for Police use.  This one has the typical Police use wear (shot little, carried a lot).  Rifling is sharp, bore is Bright, pistol operates flawlessly. December, 1997 issue date to North Rhine-Westphalia, the largest of Germany's Police forces. It has the 2nd generation feed ramp designed to handle hollow point rounds that were then being issued to Police units.  This pistol was built towards the end of Sig's contract so it has all of the upgrades that may not be found in early 1980's P6's.I have both stock plastic grips that would have been issued with the pistol, and a thicker set of very nice checkered wood Sig grips.  The wood grips are more hand fllling, the plastic are slimmer.  I've put one grip panel on each side in the pictures so you can see the difference.Von Stavenhagen sights (post and dot), 3 original welded steel Sig 8 round mags, and a set of three Wolff mainsprings to reduce the double action trigger pull.  I left the trigger pull stock, but you may wish to experiment with a lower weight spring.This is a single stack 9mm (8+1) that is about the same size as a Glock 19 or 1911 Commander.  All steel West German design and construction, exceptionally well engineered.  A great way to get into Sig's steel pistols without the $1,000+ for a P226, and without the very large grip of a double stack magazine.You can get more information about this unique pistol and its history at realgunreviewsdotcom, search P6.No warranty expressed or implied, subject to prior sale, if this ad is posted the merchandise is still available. By responding to this Ad you confirm that it is legal for you to purchase, own, and possess this merchandise.I'll need to see a current GA Drivers License, would like to see a GA Concealed Permit; I'll have both available for your inspection. Only buyers 21 and over, no shipping, but I do travel Georgia and perhaps can meet you halfway.
